  "prompt": "How do I set a default font in Gmail?",
  "response": "Unfortunately, Gmail doesn't offer a single, global setting to set a \"default font\" across your entire account. However, you can set a font style that will be used for **new emails you compose**. Here's how:\n\n**Steps to Set a Default Font for New Emails:**\n\n1.  **Open Gmail in a Web Browser:** This method works on computers, not the mobile app.\n\n2.  **Go to Settings:**\n    *   Click the **gear icon** in the top right corner of the Gmail window.\n    *   Select **\"See all settings.\"**\n\n3.  **General Tab:**  Make sure you're on the \"General\" tab.\n\n4.  **Scroll to \"Default text style\":**  Scroll down the General settings page until you find the \"Default text style\" section.\n\n5.  **Choose Your Font:**\n    *   Click the **Font name** to open the font selection menu. Choose your desired font.\n    *   Click the **Size** to choose your preferred font size (Small, Normal, Large, Huge).\n    *   Use the **B** (Bold), *I* (Italic), and **U** (Underline) buttons to set your preferred styling.\n    *   Click the **T** (Text Color) and the paint bucket (Background Color) buttons to choose your preferred colors.\n\n6.  **Save Changes:**  Scroll down to the very bottom of the page and click **\"Save Changes.\"**\n\n**Important Notes and Limitations:**\n\n*   **Applies to New Emails Only:** This setting *only* affects new emails you compose. It doesn't change the font in existing emails, or the font used when you are replying to or forwarding an email.\n\n*   **Reply/Forward Behavior:** When you reply to or forward an email, Gmail will often retain the original formatting of the message you are replying to.  This is to maintain the appearance of the original conversation. You'll need to manually change the font within your reply if you want to override it.\n\n*   **No Global Override for Everything:**  There's no single setting to force all emails (incoming, outgoing, replies, forwards) to display in a specific font.  Gmail respects the formatting set by the original sender.\n\n*   **Gmail Mobile App:** The Gmail mobile app doesn't have this \"default font\" setting.\n\n**Workarounds and Tips:**\n\n*   **Compose Window Formatting:** When composing a new email (or replying/forwarding), you can always change the font on a per-email basis using the formatting toolbar at the bottom of the compose window.\n\n*   **Copy/Paste and \"Paste without formatting\":**  If you want to force plain text, copy the text you want to send and then use the \"Paste without formatting\" option (usually Ctrl+Shift+V on Windows or Cmd+Shift+V on Mac) to paste it into your email.  Then, you can apply your preferred font using the compose window's formatting tools.\n\n*   **Browser Extensions (Use with caution):**  There *might* be some browser extensions that claim to offer more extensive font control in Gmail.  However, be extremely cautious when installing browser extensions, especially those that access your email.  Make sure the extension is from a reputable developer and has good reviews, as malicious extensions can pose a security risk.  I can't recommend any specific extension because of security concerns.\n",
